page.title: 11OLD STANWAY
page.content: { Cant's garden centre}is situated on the top of a hill. Plants flowers and shrubs are sold and so is pet food. Goldfish and birds are also sold at Cant's. Down the road is the{Swan {Inn,}opposite the Public playingfield and the{Roman river.}The Swan Inn is not only a pub but also has a restaurant and wine bar. This part of London road is quite quackers, with the Swan next door is the Cygnet stores and he greengrocers owned by Mr. and Mrs. Duckling! Opposite the Swan is a small{village {green}with a large tree and a seat around it. The tree as planted to comemorate King George V's coronation and the seat was installed to commemorate the King's Jubilee year,1935.
